Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
createBasicPathGroups(25.10)                      createBasicPathGroups(25.10)

Name
       createBasicPathGroups  -  Explicitly creates standard path groups irre-
       spective of the design stage

Syntax
       createBasicPathGroups

       [-help]

       [-expanded]

       [-reset]

       Explicitly creates standard path  groups  irrespective  of  the  design
       stage. The following path groups are created:

              * reg2reg (register-to-register)

              * reg2cgate (register-to-clock-gate)

              * default

       Note:

              * If  a  design  does  not  have any reg2reg paths, or reg2cgate
                paths,  this  command  will  create  the  corresponding   path
                group(s).

              * If  the specified path group, say reg2reg, already exists, the
                software will give the following warning:

                **WARN: (IMPOPT-3666):  Path  group  reg2reg  already  exists.
                Skipping the creation of this path group.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each createBasicPathGroups parameter.  For  a  de-
              tailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use
              the man command:  man createBasicPathGroups.

       -expanded
              When  this parameter is specified, the following path groups are
              created:

              * reg2reg

              * reg2cgate

              * in2reg

              * reg2out

              * in2out

              When this parameter is not  specified,  only  the  default  path
              groups, reg2reg and reg2cgate, are created.

              Note: Timing optimization will consider these path groups in the
              same way as paths grouped using the group_path command. In addi-
              tion,  if a design does not have any reg2reg or reg2cgate paths,
              this command will not create the corresponding path groups.

       -reset Deletes all existing path groups. This is equivalent to  running
              the reset_path_group command.

              Note:  After deleting the existing path groups, new path groups,
              reg2reg and reg2cgate are created.

Examples
              * The following command is used  to  create  the  standard  path
                groups and assigns an effort level to each group:

                createBasicPathGroups

                The software returns the following information:

                Created reg2reg path group

                Effort level <high> specified for reg2reg path_group

                Created reg2cgate path group

                Effort level <high> specified for reg2cgate path_group

              * The  following  commands are used to set the  effort level for
                the reg2reg path group to high, and report the  parameters  of
                the path groups that are created:

                setPathGroupOptions reg2reg -effortLevel low

                reportPathGroupOptions

                The software prints the following report:

                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

                |Path               Group|Effort|Adjustment(early/late)|Target
                Slack|weight|SkewingSlackCons|view               |

                ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

                |reg2reg   | high | 0.1    /-0.2         | 0          |  2   |
                0.3         |AV_HL_FUNC_MIN_RC1 |

                |reg2cgate | high | 0.2    /0            | 0          |  1   |
                0.5         |AV_HL_FUNC_MAX_RC1 |

Related Information
